# 11. それぞれの想いを抱きしめて

???: ...nade! Kanade...!
Kanade: Mm... Dad...
???: Kanade...!
Kanade: ...!
Rin: You're finally awake. Thank goodness...
Rin: Are you feeling okay, Kanade...?
Kanade: I'm okay...
Kanade: Umm... What just...?
Len: No matter how hard we tried, you wouldn't wake up. We were so worried...
Kanade: Oh, I see...
Kanade: I'm sorry for worrying you.
Mafuyu: Are you okay, Kanade?
Kanade: Yes, I'm okay.
Kanade: I was dreaming just now, I think.
Mizuki: Kanade, do you remember what that dream was about?
Mizuki: Ena and Mafuyu and I figured out we all had the same dream, it sounds like.
Kanade: The same dream...?
Ena: Yeah. From what Mafuyu said, you were a student at Miya Girls...
Ena: The three of us were able to regain our memories after listening to your song. Then, we got on Nightcord and realized that it was all just a dream...
Kanade: Oh...
Kanade: Yes, I remember that.
Kanade: In my dream...
Miku: A dream where N25 never existed...
Mizuki: I know, right?! And I dropped out of school.
Ena: Me too. I spent all my time drawing, all on my own...
Ena: The worst part was how realistic it all felt.
Kanade: I see...
Mafuyu: Still, why did we have that dream at all?
KAITO: Those black fragments are probably the answer.
Mafuyu: The fragments...?
KAITO: Yes, we realized that after you'd all fallen asleep.
KAITO: Those fragments... They were born out of the feelings which had built up in this SEKAI.
Kanade: Feelings...?
MEIKO: Yes. Pain, sadness, regret, a desire to escape... Those sorts of feelings.
MEIKO: Along with wishes that can never be granted.
Luka: But those fragments of feelings may be even more complicated than just that.
Luka: All of those messy feelings got mixed around with each other, and made one especially messy dream.
Kanade: ...
Kanade: Wishes that can never be granted...
Ena: Yeah, that's a good way to describe that dream. I mean, there's no way things would just go that well.
Mizuki: Right. Thank goodness we were able to realize the truth after listening to your song, Kanade.
Mafuyu: *Nod*
Mafuyu: Honestly, I'd rather not experience anything like that again.
Kanade: Mafuyu...
Mizuki: I get why you're worried... I mean, who knows what's gonna happen in the future?
Miku: I don't think you need to worry.
Miku: Just take a look at that...
Mafuyu: Huh...?
Mizuki: The tree's grown!
Mafuyu: And all the black fragments are gone.
Miku: This tree was born out of a wide variety of feelings, and your feelings make it grow.
Miku: Those black fragments are your feelings too...so absorbing them must've caused it to grow.
Mafuyu: Then...
Len: Th-There should be nothing to worry about...
KAITO: We're not making any promises that something like this won't happen again, though.
Kanade: I'm not worried.
Kanade: If something like this does happen again...
Kanade: No matter what kind of world we end up in, the past or the future...
Kanade: I'll find all of you again.
Ena: Kanade...
Ena: Yeah... No matter where we end up, I believe that you'll find us, Kanade.
Mizuki: Yeah, that dream showed us that for sure.
Mizuki: I believe in you too, Kanade.
Mafuyu: Me too...
Kanade: Thank you.
Kanade: Let's keep on making music together. Our music.
